<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Dev entitlements: NO sandbox.

         Under the App Sandbox, `FileManager.enumerator(at: /Volumes/Card)`
         silently returns zero items without the user granting access via
         NSOpenPanel first. Our "click card → auto-scan" UX doesn't do that
         grant dance, so sandboxed dev builds stay stuck on "Scanning…".

         The MAS submission path lives at PhotoImporter.mas.entitlements:
         turn sandbox back on + keep iCloud, and implement an explicit
         "grant access to the card" NSOpenPanel flow for the MAS build.

         For now, leave this file empty-ish so dev builds run with full
         filesystem access and Cloud-KV still works via the local
         UserDefaults fallback our CloudKVStore uses.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
